      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_GetDistributionReports",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to retrieve information about distribution reports associated with a specific distribution job. It is part of the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Scheduler",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " schema and is intended to be used in a reporting or distribution system where reports are generated and distributed based on predefined jobs. The procedure first logs context information into a separate table and then retrieves a list of reports, including details such as report names, templates, output formats, and email recipient information."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Medium"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The complexity of this stored procedure is considered medium. It involves multiple table joins, a subquery, and an external procedure call, which requires a good understanding of the database schema and relationships. The use of distinct selection and ordering adds to the complexity, though it remains manageable for someone familiar with SQL and the database structure."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
